            "id": 9668640,
            "app_id": 100468,
            "parent_sub_control_id": null,
            "sub_control_template_id": 4522,
            "title": "Audit Trails for Root or Administrative Accounts",
            "description": "<div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Overview:<\/b><\/div>Implement automated audit trails for all system components to reconstruct the following events: All actions taken by any individual with root or administrative privileges. Accounts with increased privileges, such as the &ldquo;administrator&rdquo; or &ldquo;root&rdquo; account, have the potential to greatly impact the security or operational functionality of a system. Without a log of the activities performed, an organization is unable to trace any issues resulting from an administrative mistake or misuse of privilege back to the specific action and individual. <br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Action Items:<\/b><\/div>1) Verify all actions taken by any individual with root or administrative privileges are logged. <br \/>\n2) Verify this control requirement is documented and known by all parties. <br \/>\n3) Verify that access is controlled using access control lists based on identity or role. <br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Related Documents<\/b> <span>(document name and content will vary by organization):<\/span><\/div>1) Logging &amp; Mentoring Standard<br \/>\n2) Access Control Policy<br \/>\n3) List of users with root or administrative privileges<br \/>\n4) Access Control Lists (ACLs) <br \/>\n5) Audit trails of privileged user accounts",
            "additional_guidance": "",
            "budget_amount": null,
