            "id": 9668639,
            "app_id": 100468,
            "parent_sub_control_id": null,
            "sub_control_template_id": 4521,
            "title": "Secure Audit Trails",
            "description": "<div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Overview:<\/b><\/div>Secure audit trails so they cannot be altered (unauthorized access, modification, and deletion). Often a malicious individual who has entered the network will attempt to edit the audit logs in order to hide their activity. Without adequate protection of audit logs, their completeness, accuracy, and integrity cannot be guaranteed, and the audit logs can be rendered useless as an investigation tool after a compromise. Audit trail files should always be protected from unauthorized modification. Adequate protection of the audit logs includes strong access control (limit access to logs based on &ldquo;need to know&rdquo; only), and use of physical or network segregation to make the logs harder to find and modify. <br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Action Items:<\/b><\/div>1) Interview system administrators and examine system configurations and permissions to verify that audit trails are secured so that they cannot be altered. <br \/>\n2) Interview system administrators and examine system configurations and permissions to verify that audit trails are secured so that they cannot be altered as follow: Current audit trail files are protected from unauthorized modifications via access control mechanisms, physical segregation, and\/or network segregation. <br \/>\n3) Verify this control requirement is documented and known by all parties.<br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Related Documents<\/b> <span>(document name and content will vary by organization):<\/span><\/div>1) Logging &amp; Monitoring Standard<br \/>\n2) Audit &amp; Accountability Policy<br \/>\n3) Access Control Policy and Procedures<br \/>\n4) Procedures addressing protection of audit information<br \/>\n5) List of log storage locations for information systems",
            "additional_guidance": "",
            "budget_amount": null,
            "notes": null,
