            "id": 9668656,
            "app_id": 100468,
            "parent_sub_control_id": null,
            "sub_control_template_id": 4547,
            "title": "Logging of Access to Sensitive Data",
            "description": "<div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Overview:<\/b><\/div>Implement automated audit trails for all system components to reconstruct the following events: All individual user accesses to sensitive data (e.g. cardholder data, PII, etc.). Malicious individuals could obtain knowledge of a user account with access to systems that store sensitive data, or they could create a new, unauthorized account in order to access sensitive data. A record of all individual accesses to sensitive data can identify which accounts may have been compromised or misused. Tools such as File Integrity Monitoring (FIM) or Security Information and Event Monitoring (SIEM) can be used to support this effort. <br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Action Items:<\/b><\/div>1) Verify all individual access to sensitive data (e.g. cardholder data, PII, etc.) is logged. <br \/>\n2) Verify this control requirement is documented and known by all parties. <br \/>\n3) Determine and document whether tools such as File Integrity Monitoring (FIM) or Security Information and Event Monitoring (SIEM) are employed by the organization to support this effort. <br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Related Documents<\/b> <span>(document name and content will vary by organization):<\/span><\/div>1) Logging &amp; Monitoring Standard<br \/>\n2) Audit &amp; Accountability Policy<br \/>\n3) Logs of valid\/invalid logical access attempts to systems that store sensitive data<br \/>\n4) Access Control Policy<br \/>\n5) Configurations of tools, if used, that support this effort (e.g. FIM and SIEM)",
            "additional_guidance": "",
