            "id": 9668648,
            "app_id": 100468,
            "parent_sub_control_id": null,
            "sub_control_template_id": 4537,
            "title": "Audit Trail Entry Requirements",
            "description": "<div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Overview:<\/b><\/div>Record at least the following audit trail entries for all system components for each event: User Identification; Type of Event; Date and Time; Success or Failure Indication; Origination of Event; Identity or name of affected data, system component, or resource. By recording these details for the auditable events at 10.2, a potential compromise can be quickly identified, and with sufficient detail to know who, what, where, when, and how. Not, specific logging requirements for attributes may vary by framework. <br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Action Items:<\/b><\/div>1) Through interviews and observation of audit logs, for each auditable event perform the following: Verify user identification is included in log entries<br \/>\n2) Verify type of event is included in log entries<br \/>\n3) Verify date and time stamp is included in log entries<br \/>\n4) Verify success or failure indication is included in log entries<br \/>\n5) Verify origination of event is included in log entries<br \/>\n6) Verify identity or name of affected data, system component, or resources is included in log entries<br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Related Documents<\/b> <span>(document name and content will vary by organization):<\/span><\/div>1) Logging &amp; Monitoring Standard<br \/>\n2) Sample of audit logs<br \/>\n3) Audit &amp; Accountability Policy",
