            "sub_control_template_id": 4565,
            "title": "User Activity Monitoring",
            "description": "<div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Overview:<\/b><\/div>Ensure the organization alerts when users deviate from normal login behavior, such as time-of-day, workstation location, and duration. The organization should profile each user's typical account usage by determining normal time-of-day access and access duration. Reports should be generated that indicate users who have logged in during unusual hours or have exceeded their normal login duration. This includes flagging the use of the user's credentials from a computer other than computers on which the user generally works. <br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Action Items:<\/b><\/div>1) Verify this control requirement is documented and known by all personnel. <br \/>\n2) Verify the organization alerts when users deviate from normal login behavior, such as time-of-day, workstation location, and duration.<br \/>\n3) Verify the organization profiles each user's typical account usage by determining normal time-of-day access and access duration.<br \/>\n4) Verify reports are generated that indicate users who have logged in during unusual hours or have exceeded their normal login duration.<br \/>\n5) Verify reports generated include flagging the use of the user's credentials from a computer other than computers on which the user generally works. <br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Related Documents<\/b> <span>(document name and content will vary by organization):<\/span><\/div>1) Logging &amp; Monitoring Standard<br \/>\n2) Audit &amp; Accountability Policy<br \/>\n3) Alerts generated for abnormal user login activity",
