            "id": 9668657,
            "app_id": 100468,
            "parent_sub_control_id": null,
            "sub_control_template_id": 4548,
            "title": "Logging of Access to Audit Trails",
            "description": "<div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Overview:<\/b><\/div>Implement automated audit trails for all system components to reconstruct the following events: Access to all audit trails. Malicious users often attempt to alter audit logs to hide their actions, and a record of access allows an organization to trace any inconsistencies or potential tampering of the logs to an individual account. Having access to logs identifying changes, additions, and deletions can help retrace steps made by unauthorized personnel. <br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Action Items:<\/b><\/div>1) Verify access to all audit trails is logged. <br \/>\n2) Verify that this control requirement is documented and known by all parties. <br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Related Documents<\/b> <span>(document name and content will vary by organization):<\/span><\/div>1) Logging &amp; Monitoring Standard<br \/>\n2) Audit &amp; Accountability Policy<br \/>\n3) Logs of valid\/invalid logical access attempts to audit trails<br \/>\n4) Access Control Policy",
