            "id": 9668659,
            "app_id": 100468,
            "parent_sub_control_id": null,
            "sub_control_template_id": 4550,
            "title": "Logging of  Initializing, Stopping, or Pausing of the Audit Logs",
            "description": "<div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Overview:<\/b><\/div>Implement automated audit trails for all system components to reconstruct the following events: initializing, stopping, or pausing of the audit logs. Turning the audit logs off (or pausing them) prior to performing illicit activities is a common practice for malicious users wishing to avoid detection. Initialization of audit logs could indicate that the log function was disabled by a user to hide their actions.<br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Action Items:<\/b><\/div>1) Verify the following are logged: Initialization of audit logs; stopping or pausing of audit logs.<br \/>\n2) Verify there are response procedures in place to address audit log processing failures. <br \/>\n3) Verify this control requirement is documented and known by all parties. <br \/>\n4) Verify that information systems alert the security team if an audit log process fails. <br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Related Documents<\/b> <span>(document name and content will vary by organization):<\/span><\/div>1) Logging &amp; Monitoring Standard<br \/>\n2) Audit &amp; Accountability Policy<br \/>\n3) Logs of the following events: initializing, stopping, or pausing of the audit logs<br \/>\n4) Access Control Policy<br \/>\n5) Procedures addressing response to audit processing failures",
