            "sub_control_template_id": 4543,
            "title": "Automated Port Scanning",
            "description": "<div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Overview:<\/b><\/div>Perform automated port scans on a regular basis against all key servers and compare to a known effective baseline. If a change that is not listed on the organization's approved baseline is discovered, an alert should be generated and reviewed. <br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Action Items:<\/b><\/div>1) Verify that automated port scans are performed on a regular basis against all key servers and compare to a known effective baseline<br \/>\n2) Verify that if a change is discovered that is not listed on the organization's approved baseline (unauthorized ports are detected), an alert is generated and reviewed <br \/>\n3) Verify this control requirement is documented and known by all parties <br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Related Documents<\/b> <span>(document name and content will vary by organization):<\/span><\/div>1) Logging &amp; Monitoring Standard<br \/>\n2) Audit &amp; Accountability Policy<br \/>\n3) Automated Port Scan Results<br \/>\n4) Organizational Approved Baseline outlining approved ports",
