            "sub_control_template_id": 4538,
            "title": "Adequate Storage Space for Audit Logs",
            "description": "<div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Overview:<\/b><\/div>Ensure that all systems that store logs have adequate storage space for the logs generated so that log files will not fill up between log rotation intervals. The logs must be archived and digitally signed on a periodic basis. Allocating sufficient audit storage capacity reduces the likelihood of such capacity being exceeded and resulting in the potential loss or reduction of auditing capability.<br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Action Items:<\/b><\/div>1) Verify that all systems that store logs have adequate storage space for the logs generated so that log files will not fill up between log rotation intervals<br \/>\n2) Verify that logs are archived and digitally signed on a periodic basis<br \/>\n3) Verify this control requirement is documented and known by all parties <br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Related Documents<\/b> <span>(document name and content will vary by organization):<\/span><\/div>1) Logging &amp; Monitoring Standard<br \/>\n2) Audit &amp; Accountability Policy<br \/>\n3) List of locations where logs are stored and available storage space for the logs<br \/>\n4) Procedures addressing audit storage capacity",
