            "parent_sub_control_id": null,
            "sub_control_template_id": 4531,
            "title": "Detection Roles and Responsibilities",
            "description": "<div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Overview:<\/b><\/div><p>Ensure that the organization monitors and analyzes security alerts and information, and distributes the alerts and information to appropriate personnel. Each person or team with responsibilities for information security management should be clearly aware of their responsibilities and related tasks, through specific policy. Without this accountability, gaps in processes may open access into critical resources or cardholder data. Entities should also consider transition and\/or succession plans for key personnel to avoid potential gaps in security assignments, which could result in responsibilities not being assigned and therefore not performed.<br>\n<br><\/p>\n\n<div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Action Items:<\/b><\/div><p>1) Verify that responsibility for monitoring and analyzing security alerts and distributing information to appropriate information security and business unit management personnel is formally assigned. <br>\n2) Verify that the list of users responsible for monitoring alerts and information is documented and updated as the workforce changes. <br>\n<br><\/p>\n\n<div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Related Documents<\/b> <span>(document name and content will vary by organization):<\/span><\/div><p>1) Logging &amp; Monitoring Standard<br>\n2) Audit &amp; Accountability Policy<br>\n3) List of users responsible for monitoring alerts and information<\/p>",
