            "parent_sub_control_id": null,
            "sub_control_template_id": 4526,
            "title": "Event Log Aggregation and Reporting",
            "description": "<div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Overview:<\/b><\/div>Ensure that appropriate logs are being aggregated to a central log management system for analysis and review. As part of this effort, a Security Information and Event Management (SIEM) or log analytics tool should be deployed for log correlation and analysis. Using the SIEM tool, system administrators and security personnel should devise profiles of common events from given systems so that they can tune detection to focus on unusual activity, avoid false positives, more rapidly identify anomalies, and prevent overwhelming analysts with insignificant alerts. The requirements for the specific SIEM tool or equivalent solution may vary by framework. <br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Action Items:<\/b><\/div>1) Verify that appropriate logs are being aggregated to a central log management system for analysis and review<br \/>\n2) Verify that a SIEM or log analytics tool has been deployed for log correlation and analysis<br \/>\n3) Verify that this control requirement is documented and known by all parties <br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Related Documents<\/b> <span>(document name and content will vary by organization):<\/span><\/div>1) Logging &amp; Monitoring Standard<br \/>\n2) Audit &amp; Accountability Policy<br \/>\n3) Procedures addressing audit reduction and report generation<br \/>\n4) SIEM Tool and configuration settings<br \/>\n5) Information system audit records",
