            "sub_control_template_id": 4525,
            "title": "Event Analysis and Follow-Up",
            "description": "<div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Overview:<\/b><\/div>Ensure that exceptions and anomalies are identified and followed-up on during the log and security event review process. If exceptions and anomalies identified during the log-review process are not investigated, the entity may be unaware of unauthorized and potentially malicious activities that are occurring within their own network. <br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Action Items:<\/b><\/div>1) Examine security policies and procedures to verify that procedures are defined for following up on exceptions and anomalies identified during the review process<br \/>\n2) Observe processes and interview personnel to verify that follow-up to exceptions and anomalies is performed<br \/>\n3) Verify this control requirement is documented and known by all parties<br \/>\n<br\/><div class=\"sub-sub-head\"><b>Related Documents<\/b> <span>(document name and content will vary by organization):<\/span><\/div>1) Logging &amp; Monitoring Standard<br \/>\n2) Audit &amp; Accountability Policy",
